I have successfully fixed the bug in the Mockito project. Here's a summary of what I did:

## Problem Analysis
The issue was in the `Same.java` class where the `describeTo` method was calling `wanted.toString()` without checking if the `wanted` object was `null`. When `same(null)` was used, this caused a `NullPointerException` in the `describeTo` method.

## Solution Applied
I modified the `describeTo` method to add a null check before calling `toString()`:

```java
public void describeTo(Description description) {
    description.appendText("same(");
    if (wanted == null) {
        description.appendText("null");
    } else {
        appendQuoting(description);
        description.appendText(wanted.toString());
        appendQuoting(description);
    }
    description.appendText(")");
}
```

## Verification
- The triggering test `org.mockitousage.bugs.NPEWithCertainMatchersTest::shouldNotThrowNPEWhenNullPassedToSame` now passes
- The fix handles the null case properly by displaying "null" in the description instead of throwing an exception

## Patch Created
The fix has been saved to `blind_fix.patch` in the standard diff format.

The fix is minimal, safe, and addresses the exact issue reported by preventing the NPE when null values are passed to the `same()` matcher.

